5:
So this is the combat training I've
heard so much about. Quite the
spectacle, I see.
9:
Ah, hello... Are you off to the
Kaleidoscope?
13:
Nope, just out doing some shopping.
We stopped by the Guild and heard
about your training drills.
15:
Mind if we hang around and watch
for a bit?
23:
You there! Your form is slipping.
Don't slack off just because this is
practice.
33:
I'm a bit confused as to why Trine
would wear such attire during
training, though. Is it not difficult to
move in those clo—
36:
What are you saying?! Her outfit is
VERY important to our training!
38:
Yeah! This training wouldn't be
NEARLY as effective without our
queen's—I mean, Miss Trine's
amazing training uniform!
41:
I-is that so... I apologize for my
thoughtless remark...
44:
I suppose it's fine as long as Trine's
okay with it...
48:
I struggle to understand it myself,
but it seems to boost morale, so I do
not mind.
55:
All right. We will now move onto the
next stage of our training... Field
practice in the upper levels of the
Kaleidoscope.
56:
Any monsters you encounter are
real, and so is the threat of death.
Do not let your guard down!
64:
The last group should have made
appropriate progress by now. Group
Three, are you ready?
67:
Yes! Group Three, ready for
deployment!
70: Aren't you going to join them, Trine?
73:
It will not count as training if I am
there holding their hands...
78:
I will admit that I am worried
though...
82:
The upper levels should pose no
threat to them. They have the skills.
85: So a reaper like me should not—
89:
M-Miss Trine! We've got a situation
on our hands! The first group went
ahead and—
96:
A-at the end of the training route...
They ran into an unexpectedly large
group of monsters... As we speak,
they're trying to fight them off, but—
99:
Understood. You did well to come
back to me. Now go seek medical
treatment.
103:
Stella, go tell the Guild! Light, Trine,
and I are going to go rescue the first
group!
113: I knew it... I truly am a reaper...
117: No. I can't think like this. Not now!
132: Miss Trine, look! We did it!
137:
You're all safe... Thank goodness...
Y-you did well surviving on your own!
141:
I apologize. I put you all in grave
danger—
144: N-no way! This isn't your fault!
146:
Yeah, if anything, you're the reason
we survived! We'd be toast if it
weren't for your teachings!
148:
Besides, this is the Kaleidoscope. We
all know to expect the unexpected.
150:
...So even if we didn't make it out of
here alive...
152: None of us would ever blame you!
157:
Looks like you've got yourself a
batch of resilient students here.
167:
But this isn't the time to get
emotional.
175:
But could you stick around and
guide us for a while?
179: I see no problem with that.
182: Time to take out any stragglers!
